{"履修期": "秋学期", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "Please refer to the English section.", "到達目標": "Please refer to the English section.", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "", "授業の概要・背景": "This is a high-level course. Therefore, it is advisable for students to have already taken similar high-level courses. Learners will be required to read and listen to native-level English language news and critically analyze the language within. Please be prepared to work hard and make valuable contributions to the class with high-level input.", "授業方法": "Each class will be completed entirely in English and consist of lectures, seminars, discussions, presentations and pair and group work.Google Classroom will be used for course information and assignment submissions. Therefore, students will NEED access to a computer at home or use a school computer lab to be able to properly complete and submit assignments. Desktop, laptop, notebook, Macbook, etc, are fine. Students should also have a Google account and sign up for Google Drive and Google Classroom (both are free).This course is communication-based and requires interactive English-only communication with classmates every lesson.This is an all-English classroom. Students can expect to communicate with the teacher and other students in English only. Assignments may require the use of a computer and online sites.Additionally, this class is taught communicatively and the class functions as a community in which all members support each other. This means that students can expect to interact regularly through pair work or small groups to review course content and/or will have consistent interaction with the teacher.", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<div><span style=\"font-size:13.3333px;\">ALL SESSION INFORMATION IS SUBJECT TO CHANGE AT THE TEACHER'S DISCRETION</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.3333px;\">【Startup Week】URL:https://～</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.3333px;\">\"Online class（On-demand format）\"／《90minutes》</span></div><div><span style=\"fon